\displaystyle\int_0^{\infty} \frac{\sin x}x dx = \frac \pi 2
\displaystyle\int_0^{\infty} \frac{|\sin x|}x dx \to \infty
x_n = 2\pi n + \pi / 2
\sin(x_n) = 1
\sin
x_n
\epsilon, \delta > 0
\sin(x) \ge 1 - \epsilon
|x-x_n| \le \delta
\int_0^{+\infty} \frac{|\sin x|}{x} dx \ge 2\delta\sum_{n = 0}^{+\infty} \frac{1 - \epsilon}{x_n} = \frac{2\delta(1-\epsilon)}{2\pi}\sum_{n=0}^{+\infty} \frac{1}{n + 1/4} \rightarrow \infty 
